image_text: I had a handful of ash leaves in my yard from the Walbridge fire, which was only a couple miles away from my house.
Messages in bronze and burnt offerings blown in on fiery thermals from 8-10 miles away, John estimates (big leaf maple, tan oak, bay, black oak, perhaps madrone?). Crucible times and places
Not my property, but the Oroville Wildlife Area, September 15. This would have been from the Bear fire burning up by Oroville Lake. Perhaps canyon live oak and black oak? Not sure though
